							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Unfortunatly this isn't the case here. Store bought are better then the player made in only one aspect, they are about 1/10th the price when it comes to buying them from the merchants.
<br />

<br />
Since by the time you can make a level 6 poison, you can buy a stack of level 10 poison for about the same price with no effort at all. It also is very hard to craft poisons at higher levels, they have alot of durability for such low increases per tick.
<br />

<br />
So unless they...
<br />

<br />
1) Cut the price of Suspensions by 75% (which I dont think they should do)
<br />

<br />
2) Make each poison craft up to 20 poisons per time.. (5 crude, 10 shaped, 15 normal, 20 pristine..) Which I think would be the best solution here. That would easily compare the store bought vs the player mades in both price and availability.
<br />

<br />
Then its really not worth crafting poisons right now, potions are another matter..</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
