						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Unfortunatly yes, Right now poisons are just as effective as vendor poisons. Prices can vary alot.
<br />

<br />
If you harvest every bit of your materials they will cost aprox.. in this chart of comparison.
<br />

<br />
                Crafted   |   Vendor
<br />

<br />
Tier 1 :        80c      |      6c
<br />

<br />
Tier 2 :       2s 40c   |     24c
<br />

<br />
Tier 3 :      6s  50c   |      1s
<br />

<br />
And so on, Poisons can take a very long time to craft as well, not only that but making a full stack can take close to an hour, IF you have all the ingrediants. Gathering the stuff can take hours.
<br />

<br />
Right now unless they make it so that you get 20 poisons per crafting session (when you pristine it) And 5 less every success chance under that. Following the pattern of Arrows and Throwing weapons, it would be 5 poisons for the worst possible combine, then 10 for the combine above that, 15 for the average combine, and 20 for the total combine. That would be worth it. Also They should do the same for potions and that would really make alchemy something worth the effort. Right now every bit of the lower level potions and poisons cost too much for very little effect. If we managed to make 20 of them at a time it wouldn't be so bad and maybe would allow us to set a business up out of it..
<br />

<br />
Also a relief somewhat... Not all alchemy materials are common. There are alot of recepies that need rare materials such as Coral, Silver, Copper, Lapis Lazuli, etc.. Those materials can end up costing you 30-90s each, and in the end only make 3 poisons/potions. Really, can you honestly say that spending 10-30s per potion/poison that really dosen't do much is worth it? If they raised combines to be 20 potions/poison per pristine success, that would be much better especially for these rare combines. Each Rare ingrediant would make a total of 60 potions/poisons. Or if it's similar to the others and makes 2 loam's for each material, then that would be a total of 120 potions/poisons. Which right now really would be worth it.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="Shocked" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
