							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Right now, the only difference in poisons is resistance rates. For instance when I used Acidic Massage vs Defiled Squires ( undead) it was resisted alot ( im lvl 18... my poison is green but its the only skill level available for me.. 100 skill poisons start at lvl 20). But when I tried Crypt Substance ( i think that was the neame), the resists happened much less often. 
<br />

<br />
There probably isnt alot of difference in resists when you are using a poison closer to your level though. I couldnt tell a difference. 
<br />

<br />
As far as effects go, they are all dmg. Resist and dmg is based on the level of the poison. Nothing more as far as I can tell. Some poisons MAY have a higher max with a lower min dmg proc. DPS is still the same though. For instance, one poison may do 15-20 consistently, while another may do 5-40. Really hard to determine without writign it all down. 
<br />

<br />
Ill start documenting and see what I come up with.  I think they have plans for more effects later. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
For potions, buy the 6cp versions and use them.. write down what they do. Each one cures a specific status ailment type. Some cure Cold ailments, some heat, some poison, some disease, some arcane, etc. I havent found one that prevents those ailments in the first place, but it would be hard to tell anyway. All I have found had instant effects not a buff. Havent found one that can heal HP either.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
